<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ911009-0035</DOCNO><DOCID>911009-0035.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Du Pont Co.:   Two Units Plan Staff Cuts:   In Effort to Reduce Costs</HL><DATE>10/09/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C12</SO><CO>   DD</CO><MS>BASIC MATERIALS (BSC)</MS><IN>CHEMICALS, PLASTICS (CHM)</IN><RE>DELAWARE (DE)NORTH AMERICA (NME)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   Du Pont Co. said two units plan to eliminate in excess of390 staff positions, in the chemical concern's latest move tomeet the goals of a cost-cutting plan.   The Wilmington, Del., company said its Du Pont Financeunit intends to cut annual outlays about $70 million, in partthrough streamlining measures that include acceleration of aplan to upgrade financial reporting systems, and throughcutting 210 jobs from its payroll through incentive packages.An additional 130 positions will be eliminated bytransferring some employees to other units, and cuttingcertain temporary and contract workers.</LP><TEXT>   The Du Pont division that includes its human resources,corporate planning and safety, and health and environmentalmatters similarly said it plans to cut about 180 jobs andconsolidate certain operations. It expects to achieve annualsavings of about $60 million.   The anticipated $130 million in savings will apply to acompanywide effort announced in July to reduce costs by atleast $1 billion a year.</TEXT></DOC>